Hi, [~ozawa], in ResourceTrackService we may concurrently process nodeHeartBeat() with same nodeId and responseId, they may both pass the lastResonseId check,  this will cause the lost of RM message. With the Nodelock, we could process one by one, and the above exception could be catched.
{code}
      if (remoteNodeStatus.getResponseId() + 1 == lastNodeHeartbeatResponse
          .getResponseId()) {
        LOG.info("Received duplicate heartbeat from node " +
            rmNode.getNodeAddress() + " responseId=" +
            remoteNodeStatus.getResponseId());
        return lastNodeHeartbeatResponse;
      }
{code}

actually I have not encounter the bug caused by this, but this may be a risk.
